children.subject: They have a 3 hour gap in between.
Finals on same day are doable, unless they are back-to-back, which I'd strongly advise against.

history.content: In other circumstances I'd say it's definitely doable, but if you are concerned about declaring then that should be your number one priority. I'd make 70 your only difficult class for next semester and worry about other requirements once you're declared.

CS intended sophomore here. I've done CS61A and EE16A as a freshman (tested out of 1A/B), and am currently in CS61B and the CS70 decal. I am definitely doing CS70 next semester, and thinking about doing EE16B with it (and one easy breadth plus csm70). However, I'm worried about declaring because I didn't do so hot in CS61A and CS61B is going ok but not fabulous, so I'm wondering if doing EE16B with CS70 will hurt my chances of success in CS70 (since they both have weekly homework sets and it's been a summer + semester since I did EE16A). My other thought was to do data100 with CS70, but I'm not sure if I'll get off the waitlist for data100 (I'd definitely phase 1 it, though).

I've read a lot of past posts about 61C with 70 not being ideal and also 16B and 70 not being ideal, so I'm kinda lost. Any suggestions? Thanks :)

EDIT: RIP I just realized ee16b and cs70 finals are on the same day. is this a really bad idea????
